==The Andreas Stamatiadis Era (1979)==

''Honours Won: [[Superleague Greece|Alpha Ethniki]]: 1 ([[1978â79 Alpha Ethniki|1979]])''

''Runner-up: [[Greek Football Cup|Greek Cup]]: 1 ([[1978â79 Greek Cup|1979]])''

===1978â79 season, Part II===

Under [[Andreas Stamatiadis]] AEK Athens won the [[1978â79 Alpha Ethniki|Alpha Ethniki]] and reached the final of the [[1978â79 Greek Cup|Greek Cup]].

==1980â1985==

A next generation of star players were produced by AEK Athens' Academy and made their debut during this period including [[Stelios Manolas]], Spyros Ekonomopoulos, [[Vangelis Vlachos]] and [[Lysandros Georgamlis]].

With new president Michalis Arkadis and [[Austria]]n head coach [[Helmut Senekowitsch]], AEK won the 1983 Greek Cup, beating [[PAOK FC]] 2-0 in the newly-built [[Athens Olympic Stadium]]. Thomas Mavros and 21-year old captain [[Vangelis Vlachos]] were the goalscorers.

