Giannis Pathiakakis replaced Takis Karagiozopoulos in the middle of the [[1999â2000 Alpha Ethniki|1999-00]] season but failed to achieve more than the third place in the league, yet won its twelfth Cup title by defeating [[Ionikos F.C.|Ionikos]] 3-0 in the final. The tree goals were scored by club icon Demis Nikolaidis, [[Milen Petkov]], and Christos Maladenis. Nikolaidis was later given an award by [[FIFA]]âs Fair Play committee after informing the referee that one of the goals he scored during the match was a handball.

===2000â01 season, Part I===

[[File:Tsiartas.jpg|thumb |left |175px |[[Vassilios Tsiartas|Vasilis Tsartas]], AEK's 2000 coup signing, here after a training session with [[Greece national football team|Greece]] (2005-06-21).]]

During the 2000 summer transfer period AEK Athens signed [[Greece national football team|Greek]] internationals [[Vassilios Tsiartas|Vasilis Tsartas]] and [[Theodoros Zagorakis|Theodoris Zagorakis]] who alongside Argentine [[Fernando Navas]] who joined from [[Boca Juniors]] were meant to give them the edge to win the Greek league.

In the [[2000â01 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] AEK Athens easily overcame [[Nemzeti BajnoksÃ¡g I|Hungarian]] third placed side [[Vasas SC|Vasas]] and [[Danish Superliga|Danish]] champions [[HerfÃ¸lge Boldklub|HerfÃ¸lge]] and were drawn against [[FuÃball-Bundesliga|German]] runner-up side [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]. AEK Athens secured a 4-4 away draw thanks to goal by [[Vassilis Lakis|Vasilis Lakis]], Fernando Navas (x2) and Vasilis Tsartas. In [[Athens]] aek won 2-0, goals by Navas and Tsartas, and progressed to the [[2000â01 UEFA Cup#Fourth round|Fourth round]].

In the [[2000â01 Greek Cup|Greek Cup]] [[2000â01 Greek Cup#Second round|second round]] AEK Athens was drawn against [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]. In the first leg, and while the score was 1-1, AEK Athens fans were ready to enter the field because of referee Pontikis contantly favouring Olympiacos when AEK Athens chairman Petros Stathis instructed the players to fake injuries so that the match would stop. Olympiacos won 0-2 without a match.

===Overview===

Under Pathiakakis' management the club generally perform well. They played a total of 59 matches winning 37 of them and drawing in 10 more. They scored a total of 143 goals conceding 70.

