{{main|2005â06 AEK Athens F.C. season}}

The next season the club was strengthened with [[Greece national football team|Greek]] internationals [[Vassilis Lakis|Vasilis Lakis]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=302537.html |title=AEK homecoming for Lakis |date=2005-05-16 |work=uefa.com |accessdate=}}</ref> and [[Traianos Dellas]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=342702.html |title=Dellas happy to return to AEK |date=2005-09-19 |work=uefa.com |accessdate=}}</ref> [[Georgios Alexopoulos|Giorgos Alexopoulos]], [[Stefano Sorrentino]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=315440.html |title=Sorrentino arrives at AEK |date=2005-07-07 |work=uefa.com |accessdate=}}</ref> and [[Bruno Cirillo]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=316670.html |title=AEK land Siena centre-half |date=2005-07-13 |work=uefa.com |accessdate=}}</ref>

In the [[2005â06 Alpha Ethniki|Alpha Ethniki]] AEK Athens finished second securing a place in the [[2006â07 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] [[2006â07 UEFA Champions League qualifying rounds#Third qualifying round|third qualifying round]]. The highlight was a 3-0 home win against [[Panathinaikos AO|Panathinaikos]], with all tree goal scored in the last ten minutes by [[Nikos Liberopoulos]], [[Louay Chanko]] and [[Vassilis Lakis]].

During the winter transfer period AEK Athens signed [[Emerson MoisÃ©s Costa|Emerson]].

In the [[2005â06 Greek Cup|Greek Cup]] AEK Athes reached the final for the seventh time in the last thirteen years surpassing [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]], [[Ethnikos Piraeus F.C.|Ethnikos Piraeus]], [[Niki Volos F.C.|Niki Volos]] and [[Agrotikos Asteras F.C.|Agrotikos Asteras]].

In the [[2005â06 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] [[2005â06 UEFA Cup first round|first round]] AEK Athens were unfortunate enough to draw against [[Russian Premier League|Russian]] fourth placed side [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit]] even though they were a seeded club. They managed to secure a 0-0 draw in [[Saint Petersburg]] but lost 0-1 in [[Athens]] due to a 89th minute goal by [[Andrei Arshavin]].

===Overview===
Under Santos' management the club generally performed well. They played a total of 96 matches winning 47 of them and drawing in 23 more. They scored a total of 134 goals conceding 51.

