==Training Facilities==

AEK Athens has been using an old training complex in [[Thrakomakedones]] for years.

AEK Athens moved to a new training complex in [[Spata]] on November, 2010. The complex was built using funds of AEK Athens shareholder [[Nicholas X. Notias|Nikos Notias]]. There are currently two regular pitches with two more planned for the future. The main building hosts amongst many others the team's offices, a press room and the players rooms.

